[p 
	"This is for the infamously awful NES role playing game, Heroes of the Lance, well known for its sluggish controls and boring gameplay.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The game runs from beginning to end, aiming for as fast a time as possible.  In order to do this, I avoided fighting most enemies simply by leaping through them (resulting in damage).  The only bug I've exploited is a small glitch regarding a door's location near the end of the dungeon.  You can enter a door without actually being near it.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The toughest part of making the movie was mostly just finding the route through, then following it as quickly as I could.  The only enemies that really gave me trouble were those dragons - they're tough to jump through (though I managed it once) and they hit hard.
	$LF
]p
